### Problem Description

I ran into an issue with the [_search api](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/search-search.html). When I use RRF with [sub_searches](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/rrf.html#rrf-using-sub-searches) I cannot paginate with from and size values because it returns no hits when the search continues to next values.

### Steps to Reproduce

Step 1: (Run this query to get )
`GET example-index/_search
{
    "sub_searches": [
        {
            "query": {
                "term": {
                    "text": "blue shoes sale"
                }
            }
        },
        {
            "query": {
                "text_expansion":{
                    "ml.tokens":{
                        "model_id":"my_elser_model",
                        "model_text":"What blue shoes are on sale?"
                     }
                }
            }
        }
    ],
    "rank": {
        "rrf": {
            "window_size": 50,
            "rank_constant": 20
        }
    },
"from":10,
"size":11
}`

You will get the item rank 11 but it is the same as "from":0, "size":1 (item rank # 1). Although this is wrong as described in step 2, it should return 11 items starting by the ranked item 11.

Step 2:
`GET example-index/_search
{
    "sub_searches": [
        {
            "query": {
                "term": {
                    "text": "blue shoes sale"
                }
            }
        },
        {
            "query": {
                "text_expansion":{
                    "ml.tokens":{
                        "model_id":"my_elser_model",
                        "model_text":"What blue shoes are on sale?"
                     }
                }
            }
        }
    ],
    "rank": {
        "rrf": {
            "window_size": 50,
            "rank_constant": 20
        }
    },
"from":10,
"size":5
}`

It does return No hits.

This is something fundamental as it is used for pagination purposes.

